snippet.textDisplay:
Koonj (demoiselle crane) are migratory birds. Once they were on their way to migrate in flock, One of them see some bird seeds from the land & came to earth for food. But she caught by a farmer & incarcerate in a cage. Her partner came for her to escape from incarcerate, He tried to open the cage by different ways but in vain. Then they both hug by their long neck from the bullion of the cage & killed their selves by repress their necks.
LIKE A BIRD SEPARATED FROM IT'S FLOCK. The Story Of Demoiselle Crane.
Many of our sufi poets commemorated the Demoiselle Crane (Koonj) in their poetry.
